Heart Disease Analytics – Project Demonstration Script
1. Introduction 

Hello everyone,

My name is Dhruv Singh. Today I am presenting my internship project titled "Heart Disease Analytics using Tableau".

The objective of this project is to analyze heart disease data using MySQL, Tableau, and Flask, and present meaningful insights through interactive dashboards.

2. Problem Statement 

Heart disease is one of the leading causes of death worldwide. Large healthcare datasets contain valuable information, but manual analysis is difficult. This project helps visualize patient data to identify trends and support better healthcare decisions.

3. Dataset 

The project uses the Heart Disease UCI Dataset.

Total Records: 308
Total Attributes: 15

The dataset includes:

Age
Gender
Cholesterol
Blood Pressure
Chest Pain
Exercise-Induced Angina
Heart Disease Status
Other clinical parameters
4. Database 

The dataset was imported into MySQL.

SQL operations performed include:

Creating the database
Importing the dataset
Filtering records
Aggregate queries
Data analysis using SQL
5. Tableau Dashboard 

The processed data was connected to Tableau.

The dashboard contains:

4 KPI Cards
10 Interactive Charts
5 Filters
Dashboard
Story

The dashboard helps analyze patient demographics, disease distribution, cholesterol levels, blood pressure, chest pain types, and other important indicators.

6. Web Integration 

The Tableau dashboard was integrated into a Flask web application.

This provides a simple web interface where users can access the interactive dashboard directly through a browser.

7. Performance Testing 

Performance testing confirmed that:

SQL queries executed successfully.
The dashboard loaded correctly.
Interactive filters worked smoothly.
The dataset was rendered without errors.
8. Conclusion (30–40 seconds)

In conclusion, this project demonstrates how Business Intelligence tools such as Tableau can transform healthcare data into meaningful visual insights. The interactive dashboard supports better analysis and can assist healthcare professionals in making informed decisions.

Thank you.